    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Auto-post social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Social Scheduler · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAuto-post social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress on autopilot. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual blog posts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Read Source Feed → Skip Already-Seen Posts → Keep Top Stories → Rewrite for Our Audience (AI) → Publish to Slack → Log Published Posts (Google Sheets) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social scheduler without manual effort\n- Anyone automating blog posts in content creation\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenRouter API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ecc2e648-0823-aa15-6ea1-87351881da4a",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "9ccc721e-9ac2-0c77-788f-f2d4d59c7829",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
